<br>
T'is a hard thing to comprehend, but many of these people exist, and the only protection we have against them is being able to recognize them from the get-go.<br>
<br>
Raloth - Wandering Monk of Norrath <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub44.ezboard.com/uwarninwraithlore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Warnin Wraithlore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#8B4513>(1/13/01 11:24:58 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.telusplanet.net/public/canadak/warnin1.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ah ... there will always be the dark-hearted ...</span><hr size=1> I also plan to keep a watch on the Sh!t List on Lanys.com.  I will then add those players to this list as well.  Please, this forum is not for people that only annoy us in-game, or for people we don't get along with.  It shouldn't be abused.<br>
<br>
There should be valid reasons for puting people up here.  Kill-stealing, ninja looting, harassment, etc. are good reasons, basically those who break our rules for conduct.  Also, it should be said that some people do these things without realizing.  Raloth and I have grouped with a kid a couple times, who loots like nothing else just because he is a kid and has no patience to wait for someone else to loot.  Doesn't mean he is a bad kid, just that he doesn't realize what he is doing half the time.  It just took a few friendly suggestions/reminders for it to sink in to him.<br>
<br>
Also, it is important not to judge guilds by one or two members.  The only time a guild should be listed on here is if their officers/leaders or a majority of their membership give us grief.  It isn't posible for every guild to keep tabs on every member (especially those large ones) and there may be a day when we get someone who isn't so honest and takes us for a ride and pisses off a lot of people.  That doesn't mean we are a bad guild.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I think you all know what I mean.  Don't abuse this forum, it will be moderated a bit more than most.  I.E. if someone feels a post is inappropriate I will contact the poster in private and discuss it.  it could then be deleted.<br>
<br>
I am sure no one will misuse this forum.  I for one hope it gets used very little.<br>
<br>
be well,<br>
Warnin <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub44.ezboard.com/feverquestersofnorrathfrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=2.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub44.ezboard.com/feverquestersofnorrathfrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub44.ezboard.com/feverquestersofnorrathfrm19.threadControl?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub44.ezboard.com/feverquestersofnorrathfrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub44.ezboard.com/feverquestersofnorrathfrm19.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub44.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm15">Questing<option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm16">Gatherings of the Brave<option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm17">Tales and Roleplay<option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm18">Honour Role <option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm19">Dishonourable Denizens<option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm20">General Forum<option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm21">Officers Lounge<option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm22">Guild Tavern<option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm23">Vault of the Brave<option value="everquestersofnorrathfrm24">High Council